{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/sop/gsop--gaussian_splats_generate_training_data-2.0/render_region.svg", "type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "gaussian_splats_generate_training_data", "version": "2.0", "namespace": "gsop"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Gaussian Splats Generate Training Data"], "extent": [0, 43]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Generate synthetic data suitable for training gaussian splat models."], "extent": [78, 154]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [154, 169], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You can create gaussian splat models using synthetic data (CGI). This allows for the compression and rendering optimization of high-fidelity graphics with view-dependent effects."], "extent": [169, 349]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/sop/gsop--gaussian_splats_generate_training_data-2.0/generate_training_data_example.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}, "\n", {"type": "em", "text": ["Example of a volumetric cloud converted to gaussian splats (rendered in Unity)."]}], "extent": [349, 483]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Use this node to render the viewport and generate images.bin, cameras.bin, and points3D.ply/.bin files (required for gaussian splat training)."], "extent": [483, 627]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["When the second input ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Packed Cameras"]}, " is not provided, cameras can be procedurally generated using inflation and relaxation techniques, based on the input ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Geometry to Capture"]}, ".\nThis is effective for generating gaussian splat models of a singular object (opposed to an environment)."], "extent": [627, 912]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Inflation and relaxation is not suitable to generate sufficient camera coverage in many instances. Therefore, you can also provide your own ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Packed Cameras"]}, "."], "extent": [912, 1071]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1071, 1077], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Example workflow: "], "extent": [1077, 1100]}, {"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Generate or provide your cameras. "], "extent": [1100, 1141]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Validate coverage using ", {"type": "code", "text": ["visualize_cumuluative_camera_coverage"]}, "."], "extent": [1141, 1212]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Flipbook render the viewport (using the provided button)."], "extent": [1212, 1276]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Save the training data."], "extent": [1276, 1306]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Train your test gaussian splat model."], "extent": [1306, 1350]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Iterate as necessary."], "extent": [1350, 1378]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["When you're happy, use your final ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Packed Cameras"]}, " to perform higher quality renders."], "extent": [1378, 1470]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Set ", {"type": "code", "text": ["camera_resolution"]}, " according to your final render resolution."], "extent": [1470, 1543]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Save training data again."], "extent": [1543, 1575]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Train your final model."], "extent": [1575, 1606]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1606, 1614], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Geometry to Capture"], "extent": [1614, 1636], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The polygonal geometry you would like to generate camera coverage for."], "extent": [1636, 1712]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Packed Cameras"], "extent": [1712, 1728], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Geometry with point attributes describing camera transforms. Each point should represent one camera."], "extent": [1728, 1838]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The following point attributes can be used:"], "extent": [1838, 1886]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["N (the forward/aim vector of the camera)"], "extent": [1886, 1933]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["orient (the quaternion rotation of the camera)"], "extent": [1933, 1991]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Initialization Points"], "extent": [1991, 2014], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The points to use for gaussian splat training initialization. \n    When using real-world data, initialization points are generated using structure from motion (SfM), generally derived from COLMAP. \n    However, when generating synthetic gaussian splat models, we can source our initialization points in a number of ways. "], "extent": [2014, 2345]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [2345, 2354], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use a combination of Scatter and Points from Volume to generate a suitable initialization set. \n        50-100k points work well for object-centric scans. \n        If you intend to deform your trained splat models, a surface-based initialization set may work best."], "extent": [2354, 2636]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Color (Cd) is not required, but may produce better trained results if provided. "], "extent": [2636, 2726]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2726, 2735], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Geometry to Capture"], "extent": [2735, 2757], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The input geometry (with coverage visualizer, if enabled)."], "extent": [2757, 2821]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Packed Cameras"], "extent": [2821, 2837], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Point geometry describing a set of cameras. Each point represents one camera, containing the following attributes:"], "extent": [2837, 2961]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["N"], "extent": [2961, 2969]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["forward (note: forward is the inverse of N)"], "extent": [2969, 3019]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["up"], "extent": [3019, 3028]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["orient"], "extent": [3028, 3041]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["euler (a convenience vector attribute for rotation channel expressions)"], "extent": [3041, 3119]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["xform (matrix4)"], "extent": [3119, 3146]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Outputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [3146, 3158], "body": [{"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Camera Pose Settings"], "extent": [3158, 3186], "body": [{"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mesh Settings"], "extent": [3186, 3209], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Inflation is based on VDB and the Peak SOP. "], "extent": [3209, 3256]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Voxel Size"], "extent": [3256, 3268], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The size of the voxel for internal VDB construction. "], "extent": [3288, 3347]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "voxelsize"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Dilation Amount"], "extent": [3347, 3364], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount (in voxels) to dilate the internally created VDB volume. "], "extent": [3394, 3472]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "dilation_amount"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Remesh Target Size"], "extent": [3472, 3496], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The goal distance between cameras. Determines the number of cameras generated\n    (Target edge length for the internal Remesh SOP.)"], "extent": [3529, 3670]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [3670, 3679], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Aim for fewer than 300 cameras for the best ratio of quality and processing time."], "extent": [3679, 3770]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "remesh_target_size"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Peak Settings"], "extent": [3770, 3792], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Pre-smooth N Strength"], "extent": [3792, 3816], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to smooth N (normals) before further inflating the mesh. This helps produce evenly distributed cameras."], "extent": [3852, 3976]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "pre_smooth_n_strength"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Peak Distance"], "extent": [3976, 3991], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to inflate the mesh by its normals. Useful to push the cameras away from the target capture geometry."], "extent": [4019, 4141]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "peak_distance"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Settings"], "extent": [4141, 4162], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim at Center"], "extent": [4162, 4178], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use this toggle to force each camera to aim at the center of the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Geometry to Capture"]}, "."], "extent": [4206, 4303]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "aim_at_center"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Smooth N Strength"], "extent": [4303, 4322], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to smooth the camera aim vector (N). \n    A lower value will generate more geometry-aware camera angles, but could lead to under-sampling. \n    A higher value will produce more evenly distributed camera aim vectors, but may reduce coverage in some areas."], "extent": [4354, 4629]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "smooth_n_strength"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Remove Tilt"], "extent": [4629, 4642], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to remove the tilt of each camera. A value of 1 produces cameras angles that are strictly horizontal. "], "extent": [4668, 4788]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "remove_tilt"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["General Settings"], "extent": [4788, 4813], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to relax camera positions, after all other operations. This helps produce evenly distributed cameras."], "extent": [4844, 4962]}], "attrs": {"id": "relax_iterations"}}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sort Cameras"], "extent": [4962, 4976], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use this to simulate a camera animation trajectory which rotates around the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Geometry to Capture"]}, " in clockwise order, starting from the bottom and ending at the top.\n    Useful to temporally analyze overall camera coverage (as if you had recorded video for a physical scan)."], "extent": [5003, 5283]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sort_cameras"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Settings (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Packed Cameras"]}, " input2)"], "extent": [5283, 5328], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Mode"], "extent": [5328, 5338], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Camera aim strategy."], "extent": [5357, 5387]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use Orient: use the quaternion orient attribute to specify camera rotation."], "extent": [5387, 5469]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use Normal: use the N attribute to specify the aim vector. The up vector is computed automatically using cross product with the world up vector. "], "extent": [5469, 5621]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Aim at Center: use the center of the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Geometry to Capture"]}, " to determine camera aim. Only the P point attribute is required."], "extent": [5621, 5756]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "aim_mode"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Remove Tilt"], "extent": [5756, 5769], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to remove the tilt of each camera. A value of 1 produces cameras angles that are strictly horizontal. "], "extent": [5802, 5925]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "remove_tilt_packed"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Camera Settings"], "extent": [5925, 5947], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Preview Camera Geometry"], "extent": [5947, 5973], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable this to preview camera geometry for each camera point."], "extent": [6006, 6077]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "preview_camera_geo"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Color"], "extent": [6077, 6085], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The color to be used for camera geometry."], "extent": [6112, 6163]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "camera_color"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Camera Geometry Size"], "extent": [6163, 6185], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The scale for all camera geometry."], "extent": [6221, 6265]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "camera_geometry_scale"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Create Camera"], "extent": [6265, 6280], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Press this convenience button to create a new camera and automatically set the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["camera_path"]}, " parameter. "], "extent": [6309, 6423]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [6423, 6433], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["For your convenience, channel expressions will be logged to the console. These expressions are used to constrain the position, rotation, focal length, and resolution of the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["camera_path"]}, " camera."], "extent": [6433, 6645]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [6645, 6654], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["You can easily import this camera into LOPs using the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["sceneimportcameras"]}, " LOP."], "extent": [6654, 6747]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "create_camera:"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Camera Path"], "extent": [6747, 6760], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The camera operator path for which to look through/preview camera animation and render the viewport.\n    This is also used to compute the cumulative camera coverage of your ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Geometry to Capture"]}, "."], "extent": [6786, 6987]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "camera_path"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Focal Length"], "extent": [6987, 7002], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Sets the focal length of the camera assigned to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["camera_path"]}, ". This will affect the camera coverage visualization."], "extent": [7029, 7153]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [7153, 7162], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 9, "text": ["Recommended value for best detail to coverage ratio: 22-28."], "extent": [7162, 7232]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "focal_length"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Camera Resolution"], "extent": [7232, 7251], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The camera/image resolution (width x height) to use for your final renders."], "extent": [7284, 7373]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [7373, 7382], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["There are diminishing returns at resolutions > 1600 in final trained models."], "extent": [7382, 7476]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "camera_resolution:"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Look Through Camera"], "extent": [7476, 7497], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Press this convenience button to quickly look through and lock the camera (specified in ", {"type": "code", "text": ["camera_path"]}, ") to the active viewport. \n    This happens automatically when using the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["render_flipbook"]}, " button."], "extent": [7522, 7727]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "use_camera"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Set Frame Range"], "extent": [7727, 7744], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Press this to automatically configure the playbar / timeline based on the number of packed cameras."], "extent": [7774, 7883]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [7883, 7893], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["GSOPs assumes a frame starting number of ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0001"]}, ", therefore frame 1 is the first when using this button!"], "extent": [7893, 8010]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "set_frame_range"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Date Generation Settings"], "extent": [8010, 8042], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Data Directory"], "extent": [8042, 8059], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The directory to save viewport render images, camera.bin, images.bin, and points3D.ply. \n    This should be in the root data directory of the gaussian splat training repo location (e.g., ../gaussian-splatting-Windows/data/{})."], "extent": [8088, 8324]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "data_directory"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Image Prefix"], "extent": [8324, 8338], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The image prefix for flipbook renders. "], "extent": [8365, 8414]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "image_prefix"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Image Type"], "extent": [8414, 8426], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The file extension used for the flipbook renders."], "extent": [8451, 8514]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [8514, 8523], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["If you'd like to used Alpha masked images for training very clean models in Postshot or NerfStudio/Gsplat, prefer *.png."], "extent": [8523, 8661]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [8661, 8671], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["After changing this extension, you should re-render your scene and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["save training data"]}, ". This ensures the data types match across files."], "extent": [8671, 8821]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "image_type"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Render Flipbook"], "extent": [8821, 8838], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Press this button to flipbook render the viewport for rapid training validation loops. \n    Images are saved in {data_directory}/images."], "extent": [8868, 9014]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [9014, 9023], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["for best results, disable the grid, and ensure your current viewport has all visualizers disabled. "], "extent": [9023, 9137]}], "container": true}, {"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [9137, 9146], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["A sample resolution of ~720\u00d7720 produces quality results and rapid training times (~1 minute for 7k iterations on a 3800 using 300 images)."], "extent": [9146, 9303]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "render_flipbook"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Override Initialization Point Color"], "extent": [9303, 9340], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable this to set or override the color of initialization points. \n    Color is optimized during gaussian splat training, and is therefore not strictly required. "], "extent": [9390, 9563]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [9563, 9572], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Accurately colored points are preferable. However, white points will often reconstruct accurately."], "extent": [9572, 9688]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "override_initialization_point_color"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Camera & Images Type"], "extent": [9688, 9710], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The data type you would like to export the COLMAP-formatted ", {"type": "code", "text": ["cameras"]}, " and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["images"]}, " files."], "extent": [9743, 9842]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["bin: COLMAP model data type. Useful for NerfStudio (Splatfacto) and Postshot."], "extent": [9842, 9926]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["txt: ASCII COLMAP model data type. Larger file size, but simpler to read and debug."], "extent": [9926, 10021]}], "container": true}, {"type": "warning_group", "body": [{"type": "warning", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [10021, 10034], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["It is generally recommended to use the same file type for cameras, images, and points3D!"], "extent": [10034, 10140]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "camera_images_type"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Points3D Type"], "extent": [10140, 10155], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The data type you would like to export the initialization points as."], "extent": [10183, 10261]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["bin: COLMAP model data type. Useful for NerfStudio (Splatfacto) and Postshot."], "extent": [10261, 10345]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["txt: ASCII COLMAP model data type. Larger file size, but simpler to read and debug."], "extent": [10345, 10435]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["ply: Default data type used by Inria\u2019s 3DGS implementation. This format can be imported by many applications."], "extent": [10435, 10556]}], "container": true}, {"type": "warning_group", "body": [{"type": "warning", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [10556, 10569], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["It is generally recommended to use the same file type for cameras, images, and points3D!"], "extent": [10569, 10676]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "points3D_type"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Save Training Data"], "extent": [10676, 10697], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Press this button to export all required (COLMAP-compatible) training data:"], "extent": [10730, 10815]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["{data_directory}/sparse/0/cameras.{camera_images_type}"], "extent": [10815, 10876]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["{data_directory}/sparse/0/images.{camera_images_type}"], "extent": [10876, 10941]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Initialization Points"]}, " input is provided:"], "extent": [10941, 10996]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["{data_directory}/sparse/0/points3D.{points3D_type}"], "extent": [10996, 11058]}], "container": true}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [11058, 11067], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Using this approach means you do not need to use COLMAP/SfM to generate initialization points. \n        If you do use the Gaussian Splatting ", {"type": "code", "text": ["convert.py"]}, " script, be sure to import and align your SfM point cloud (see embedded node: ", {"type": "code", "text": ["SFM_MODEL_ALIGNMENT_EXPORT"]}, "), then ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Save Training Data"]}, ". \n        This provides the most accurate camera information for training."], "extent": [11067, 11443]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "save_training_data"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Camera File"], "extent": [11443, 11456], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The file to save packed cameras to. "], "extent": [11482, 11528]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "camera_file"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Export Packed Cameras"], "extent": [11528, 11551], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Press this button to save the packed cameras to disk. Useful for caching or I/O with other 3D software."], "extent": [11587, 11696]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "export_packed_cameras"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Visualization Settings"], "extent": [11696, 11725], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Visualize Cumulative Camera Coverage"], "extent": [11725, 11764], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable this to preview the overall camera coverage metrics for the provided ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Geometry to Capture"]}, ". \n    This is useful to validate your camera configuration before training. "], "extent": [11804, 11988]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/sop/gsop--gaussian_splats_generate_training_data-2.0/generate_training_data_coverage_visualization.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}, "\n    ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Previewing camera coverage with a range of 20-40."]}], "extent": [11988, 12119]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [12119, 12128], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The more cameras that see/render every part of the mesh, the better your trained results. Aim for a minimum of 10 cameras throughout your mesh."], "extent": [12128, 12289]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Coverage is computed as follows:"], "extent": [12289, 12326]}, {"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["For each camera, identify points inside the view frustum. "], "extent": [12326, 12391]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["For points inside the view frustum, cast a ray to the camera, checking for intersections. If the ray does not produce a hit, the point is considered visible to the camera."], "extent": [12391, 12569]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Accumulate the visibility metric for each point."], "extent": [12569, 12629]}], "container": true}, {"type": "warning_group", "body": [{"type": "warning", "indent": 4, "text": [" "], "role": "item", "extent": [12629, 12643], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Disable before rendering the viewport for improved performance!"], "extent": [12643, 12720]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "visualize_camera_coverage"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Camera Coverage Stats"], "extent": [12720, 12743], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A statistical display of the camera coverage (visibility) metric. Useful for analyzing the spread of coverage across the mesh. \n    For consistent results, aim for a lower standard deviation and high mean/median."], "extent": [12779, 13001]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "camera_coverage_stats"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Visibility Min/Max"], "extent": [13001, 13021], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The minimum and maximum number of cameras for visualization. \n    Regions with coverage of 10 cameras or fewer will likely produce holes and blurry results in trained models."], "extent": [13054, 13238]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "visibility_min_max"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Color Ramp"], "extent": [13238, 13250], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The colors used to visualize camera coverage."], "extent": [13275, 13333]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "color_ramp"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"leve